posts.title: Wester North Carolina
posts.content:
I live in the Great Smoky Mountains of NC. Here are some facts:

The area received from 10-30” of rain after 2 months of drought, much of that in the 2 days leading up to the arrival of the hurricane. 20-30mph winds came as the hurricane arrived, not coast level winds for sure but it was magnified while passing through the mountains. Ever been in Chicago or NYC when it’s windy? Mt Mitchel recorded winds over 100mph.

All of the rain, followed by the wind made massive trees fall. Some on houses and even more on power lines. All the water, of course, flowed downhill, concentrating in low lying areas, which is where a majority of the population lives. Flash floods occurred throughout the area..TN/NC/SC/GA. The dept of transportation declared all roads in western NC closed. Flash floods have not only destroyed property, but also taken many lives.

Power is out for at least half the homes, with no idea when it will be restored. Our Fire Chief estimated it would be weeks. All communication is out…all. No 9-1-1 service, no land lines, cell service, no internet. We cannot communicate with each other, or outside family and friends. Some of us have generators, but will soon run out of fuel. Maybe we will be able to re-fuel, maybe not. Some of us have Starlink and can communicate…thank you Elon!

Most homes are on wells, so no power means no water. Stores with power are open, but can only accept cash.

No sign of help from any government entity. NONE! There are power trucks around and they are working…thank God. But with such wide spread impact, it could be weeks until power is restored.

Our main roads are in the valleys, many have been damaged. Bridges gone or damaged. You can’t always take another route, because there isn’t one, or it could add a hundred miles to a short trip.

We are a tough lot and will be fine, but recovery will take years. Most of us expected the government would be AWOL. But we don’t care, we will take care of each other and fix our own mess.
